                    Joining the Keepers of Telberin
                    -------------------------------

	Joining the Keepers of Telberin is not as simple as it is in
most guilds. The joining is more of a ritual than anything else. According
to information available in the study on the third floor of Castle Telberin,
the player must ask Vilgurn for his blessing. This can only be done if the
player is polite enough to introduce to him and to sit at his desk before
asking for the blessing. The blessing will only be given to positively
aligned elves.
	Once the player has the blessing (the leather belt described 
above), the player can then go down to the throne room (th5.c). Depending
on whether the player wants to be a cleric or warrior, the player can
then type 'show belt to queen' or 'show belt to king', respectively. This
completes the ritual, and the royal member then gives the player the
dagger, while the guild_server.c takes care of the dirtywork of adding
the soul/shadow to the player. At this point the player is a member of
the Keepers of Telberin.


			GUILD TAX BREAKDOWN
			-------------------

The Keepers of Telberin have a 2% Guild Tax.

/d/Emerald/common/guild/kot/room/kot_hq2.c (Cleric Training Room)

